summary:
Here is a clear and concise summary of the Security Council document:

The Security Council,
 Recalling its previous resolutions 1503 (2003) and 1534 (2004),
 Adopts the following:

1. Decides to extend the terms of office of ad litem judges to finish specific cases:
    (a) Judge Rasoazanany and Judge Swart to finish the Hadžihasanović case;
    (b) Judge Brydensholt and Judge Eser to finish the Orić case;
    (c) Judge Thelin and Judge Van Den Wyngaert to finish the Limaj case;
    (d) Judge Canivell to finish the Krajišnik case;
    (e) Judge Szénási to finish the Halilović case, if appointed;
    (f) Judge Hanoteau to finish the Krajišnik case, if appointed;

2. Takes note of the International Tribunal's intention to finish the cases by the following deadlines:
    - Hadžihasanović case: end of September 2005
    - Halilović case: end of October 2005
    - Orić and Limaj cases: end of November 2005
    - Krajišnik case: end of April 2006
